	abstract = {Methods. We used asteroseismic rotational inversions to probe the internal stellar rotation proﬁles in red-giant models from the base of the red-giant branch up to the luminosity bump. We used the inversion method of multiplicative optimally localised averages to assess how well internal and surface rotation rates can be recovered from diﬀerent mode sets and diﬀerent synthetic rotation proﬁles.
