re discussed. We find that the standard big bang nucleosynthesis predicted lithium abundance that corresponds to the deuterium abundance inferred from observations of high-redshift, low-metallicity {QSO} absorbers requires halo star lithium depletion in an amount consistent with that from our models of rotational mixing but inconsistent with no depletion.},
