sh}{textlessSUB}{\textbackslash}textgreaterbol{\textbackslash}textless/{SUB}{\textbackslash}textgreater{\textbackslash}{textlessSUP}{\textbackslash}textgreater-1/2{\textbackslash}textless/{SUP}{\textbackslash}textgreater in the color range 0.5 \&lt;{\textbackslash}textasciitilde B-V \&lt;{\textbackslash}textasciitilde 1.5. Our results imply that - for non-saturated coronae - the L{\textbackslash}{textlessSUB}{\textbackslash}textgreaterx{\textbackslash}textless/{SUB}{\textbackslash}textgreater - P{\textbackslash}{textlessSUB}{\textbackslash}textgreaterrot{\textbackslash}textless/{SUB}{\textbackslash}textgreater relation is equivalent to the L{\textbackslash}{textlessSUB}{\textbackslash}textgreaterx{\textbackslash}textless/{SUB}{\textbackslash}textgreater/L{\textbackslash}{textlessSUB}{\textbackslash}textgreaterbol{\textbackslash}textless/{SUB}{\textbackslash}textgreater vs. R{\textbackslash}{textlessSUB}{\textbackslash}textgreatere{\textbackslash}textless/{SUB}{\textbackslash}textgreater relation. Tables 1 and 2 are only available in electronic form at {\textbackslash}textbackslash http://www.edpsciences.org},
